
terrafrom init
terraform plan
terraform plan -input=false
terraform state list
terraform state rm aws_dynamodb_table.dynamodb-terraform-state-lock  - To remove particular state from terrafrom
-------------
$ terraform state rm aws_dynamodb_table.dynamodb-terraform-state-lock
Removed aws_dynamodb_table.dynamodb-terraform-state-lock
Successfully removed 1 resource instance(s).
-------------
terraform apply
terraform apply --auto-approve
terraform -var-file= (-var switch or using --var-file for tfvars)
terraform plan --var-file dev.tfvars

terraform fmt  - To valiate and correct syntax automatically

terraform validate   - To validate format

terraform TRACE\DEBUG\ERROR\WARN\INFO  -- debugging and logging in terraform
----------------------------------
PowerShell
> $env:TF_LOG="TRACE"
> $env:TF_LOG_PATH="terraform.txt"

Bash
$ export TF_LOG="TRACE"
$ export TF_LOG_PATH="terraform.txt"


unset file_name   - to delete env varible
-----------------------------------

Workspaces:

terraform workspace new dev;  terraform workspace new uat;  terraform workspace new prod;  terraform workspace list;
terraform workspace list
terraform workspace select dev
terraform workspace show
terraform apply --var-file ./dev.tfvars
terraform workspace select uat
terraform apply --var-file ./uat.tfvars
terraform workspace select prod
terraform apply --var-file ./prod.tfvars
terraform import aws_vpc.default vpc-0649bb7f79462f2e9
